If you started vaccination last year or earlier, you will have to pay for the following vaccinations yourself.
The first dose of the vaccine should be administered between the 3rd and 5th month of the child.
Last year, a quarter of families voluntarily vaccinated their children against pneumococcal disease.
However, the parents paid 1,600 crowns or more for a dose.
The vaccination of the youngest requires four doses.
Experts estimate that every year health insurance spends 300 to 450,000 kroner on vaccine doses.
However, they save on the medical care that unvaccinated children would need.
So far, the state has spent around 500,000 kroner a year on all vaccinations for children.
The reimbursed vaccination was introduced with the "Janota package".
Pneumococci are the cause of inflammation of the middle ear but also of serious infections including meningitis and blood poisoning.
According to hospital surveys, there are up to 28 deaths of children under 10 years of age caused by pneumococcal infections.
Aside from the Czech Republic, about 40 other countries have introduced the refunded vaccination.
