I think this is a direction that needs to be followed now, Kalovsk<0xC3><0xBD> said.
But the Ministry of Health does not want to change the process of vaccination against pneumococcal pneumonia.
We are not considering it at all at the moment, his spokesman Vlastimil Sr<0xC5><0xA1>e<0xC5><0x88> said.
The optional vaccination has its drawbacks, say the doctors.
Hana Cabrnochov<0xC3><0xA1>, president of the Specialized Society of Paediatricians, acknowledges that a vaccination based on volunteerism has its flaws.
