Turkish Justice Dissolves Pro-Kurdish Party, Heavy Consequences Decision
The Turkish Constitutional Court on Friday ruled the dissolution of the country’s main pro-Kurdish party, a decision that was immediately followed by demonstrations of anger in the Kurdish community, in the south-east of the country and in Istanbul.
This decision could greatly complicate the task of the government, which has just reached out to the Kurdish community to try to end 25 years of conflict.
