Why our brain makes this kind of cabriolet is still a puzzle for researchers.
Exceptional situations can cause everyone to temporarily lose their perception of reality, according to Fuchs.
But only a small number of people will develop a psychosis.
There seems to be a genetic predisposition to schizophrenia, but studies on twins have shown that genes are not the only determining factors.
The researchers assume that the individuals concerned have minor brain damage.
It is assumed that neuronal maturation of the brain is disrupted at an early stage of development, for example, by a viral infection of the mother during pregnancy, explains Fuchs.
